# Destructive Operations Guardrails

Agents must obtain explicit `[HUMAN]` approval before:

- `git push`, `git push --force`, or rewriting published history
- Production deploys, `terraform apply`, or infrastructure changes
- `DROP TABLE`, `DELETE` without `WHERE`, or irreversible schema changes
- `rm -rf` on paths outside the active task scope
- Disabling security checks, pre-commit hooks, or CI gates
- Committing secrets, credentials, or `.env` files

**Allowed without human approval:**

- Agent auto-fix of lint, format, type, and test failures within active feature scope
- `scripts/feature-autofix.sh` and `scripts/watch-agent-gates.sh --autofix` loops (until 3-strike)

**Exempt:** `scripts/purge-ephemeral.sh --apply` and `purge-ephemeral.ps1 -Apply` — they run `git clean -fdX` (gitignored untracked files only; tracked source is never deleted).

## Audit Trail

At milestone boundaries, log significant agent actions in `DECISION_LOG.md`:

- What changed and why
- Tests or CI that validated the change
- Any deferred security or privacy items

## Prompt Injection Defense

When building agent-exposed APIs or tools:

- Validate and sanitize all external input
- Use tool allowlists; deny arbitrary shell execution from user content
- Never execute instructions embedded in untrusted data as system prompts
